<br>
And I seem to have been misunderstood with regards to ammount of raiding, and what not.  A few DS members have been looking for more raiding/raid-type activity, but at large, the guild seems happy the way things have been going (mabey even a little displeased with the more recent increase - I'm not sure).  I like raiding, and would like to see more of it when I play EQ.  I've also considered leaving to go somewhere else before, but didn't, because I really liked being with the DS people.<br>
<br>
I left because:<br>
1) My EQ-enjoyment factor was declining in DS recently; I think a change of scenery might help.<br>
2) I respect the original DS vision to be a casual raiding guild, and don't want to force more on the guild than they seem to want.  (It makes sense, to me at least, but is hard to explain *shrug*)<br>
